  "texts": [
    "District Judge David Carter: I regard myself as a social progressive and all the economists in attendance, from my perspective, had Neanderthal views on race and social policy.",
    "The basic lesson I learned.. is that social good comes at a price, a social and economic cost.",
    "I had never thought that through before being exposed to Henry's teachings.",
    ".... [It] has led me to measure the cost of the social good being furthered against the gain to be achieved.",
    "District Judge Anthony Alaimo: There is a wide area of decision entrusted to us where the result can go either way, depending on how we view the evidence."
  ],
